info.name: Data_access_model_for_malaria_awareness_in_Rwanda
info.description: **Introduction** This is an API created to demonstrate a Data Access Model for Malaria Awareness in Rwanda. **Overview of the endpoints:**Generally, the endpoints' URLs are defined using this pattern, where the values enclosed in {{}} are variables: (This example is for a URL that retrieves particular entries that have the same value in a column of a certain table) `http://{{ domain_name}}:{{ port}}/tables/{{ table_name}}/{{ column_name}}/{{ key}}` The table below shows examples of values each variable can take: | Variable | Value | | --- | --- | | domain_name | localhost | | port | 3000 | | table_name | **patient** (can also be any table name present in the database) | | column_name | **health_center_id** (can also be any column name present in the database table) | | key | 90 (can also be any other value present in the table's column) | Each endpoint has it's own corresponding URL whose parts (variables) will be defined, considering what it's meant to serve. **Authorization & authentication:** Excluding the root endpoint (`http://{{ domain_name}}:{{ port}}/`), other endpoints need authentication, which is done through inputing the `Authorization` header with credentials as its value (such as `{"email":"`[1000@gmail.com]()`","password":"qwert2000"}`) in the request.

request.description:
This endpoint sends a hello world message.

The URL follows this structure:

`http://{{ domain_name}}:{{ port}}`

The table below shows examples of values each variable can take:

| Variable | Value |
| --- | --- |
| domain_name | localhost |
| port | 3000 |

response.name: root example
response.body:
Hello world!

Welcome to the Data Access System for Malaria Awareness in Rwanda!

request.description: This endpoint retrieves the whole table. request.description: Returns random samples from the table with a number equal to the "batch_size". It excludes those in "previous_indexes" (see the `Body` of the request example shown here below). The URL follows this structure: `http://{{ domain_name}}:{{ port}}/tables/{{ table_name}}/sampling` The table below shows examples of values each variable can take: | Variable | Value | | --- | --- | | domain_name | localhost | | port | 3000 | | table_name | **patient** (can also be any table name present in the database) | Authentication is needed for access, which is done through inputing the `Authorization` header with credentials as its value (such as `{"email":"`[1000@gmail.com]()`","password":"qwert2000"}`) in the request.

Returns entries whose values in "date" column are in the specified range (see the `Body` of the request example shown here below). The URL follows this structure: `http://{{ domain_name}}:{{ port}}/tables/{{ table_name}}/timefilter` The table below shows examples of values each variable can take: | Variable | Value | | --- | --- | | domain_name | localhost | | port | 3000 | | table_name | **case_cache** (or **blood_test**) | Authentication is needed for access, which is done through inputing the `Authorization` header with credentials as its value (such as `{"email":"`[1000@gmail.com]()`","password":"qwert2000"}`) in the request.

This retrieves particular entries that have the same value in a column of a certain table. `http://{{ domain_name}}:{{ port}}/tables/{{ table_name}}/{{ column_name}}/{{ key}}` The table below shows examples of values each variable can take: | Variable | Value | | --- | --- | | domain_name | localhost | | port | 3000 | | table_name | **patient** (can also be any table name present in the database) | | column_name | **health_center_id** (can also be any column name present in the database table) | | key | 90 (can also be any other value present in the table's column) | Access to this endpoint needs authentication, which is done through inputing the `Authorization` header with credentials as its value (such as `{"email":"`[1000@gmail.com]()`","password":"qwert2000"}`) in the request.
